super smash brothers is in many ways the epitome of random violence. and it's a game that's rated for children. <br>
now, i will admit it's not graphic, but i don't think you can say that it has no effect on kids who play it. this doesn't mean they will go to their school and start beating everyone on the playground, but violence portrayed in any manner always has some effect on those who watch it or play a game with it. <br>
ever notice how little kids get more aggressive after watching loony tunes? it doesn't last but there is an effect. <br>
i don't think that we should put warning labels on games like super smash brothers but perhaps more people should be aware that (particularly with young children) what we watch and play does have an effect on us, and not always for the better. <br>
so, that's my two cents. <br>
